profile_positions.description:
Consular Legislation Sector:
•	responsible for Electoral Affairs; focal point with Foreign Electoral Registry of Brazil; elaboration of informative documents and files on the subject, updating of the Ministry´s internal information system on the subject and of the Consular and Judicial Service Manual regarding Electoral Affairs;
•	Forwarding requests for corrections in Civil Registries and Notarial Acts to the Brazilian Embassies and Consulates;
•	Responses to letters from external stakeholders (Courts of Justice, Notaries, Federal Public Attorney´s Office, etc.) and internal processes;
•	Organization of the sector's work routines (responses and maintenance of the e-mail box dac.legislação@itamaraty.gov.br, orientation of the Division's Entry and Exit Protocol, etc.)
•	Supervision of interns (guidance on automatic responses to external queries to the sector's e-mail, on reception of documents received from the Embassies and Consulates and referrals to stakeholders in Brazil, such as TRE, CEF, SRF, INSS, amongst others);
•	Participation in a mental health promotion project for the Ministry of External Relations in partnership with the Ministry´s Medical Service.
